SIMPLE: player
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Player
<hw>Play"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
plays, or amuses himself; one without serious aims; an idler; a
trifler.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who plays any game.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A dramatic actor.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who plays on an instrument of music.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A cunning <xex>player</xex> on a harp.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>1 Sam. xvi.
16.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A gamester; a gambler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>player piano</ent>⟦br⟧
